# UX Writing

When writing or editing user-facing copy in the dashboard, follow `.agents/skills/ux-writing/SKILL.md`.

## Quick reference

- Direct and technical, but human — no corporate filler, no apologies in errors
- Sentence case everywhere
- Buttons: action verbs ("Check my sites", "Sign in", "Delete site")
- Toasts: mirror the button; success in past tense; errors say what failed + how to fix
- Form errors: [what's wrong] + [how to fix it], inline
- Empty states: invitation to act, not absence report
- Terms: "Site", "Metrics", "Alert" — use consistently
